      "name": "Hemolysis model adequacy supported by published literature survey",
      "description": "A comprehensive review of peer-reviewed publications on CFD-based hemolysis prediction in centrifugal blood pumps was conducted. Seventeen studies were identified that employed the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model under comparable shear-stress and exposure-time regimes. The review concluded that the model form and numerical approach are consistent with accepted practice and that predicted RH values fall within the range reported across published pump geometries. This literature survey is considered sufficient to establish model credibility for the MRL 2 context.",
